Name: NHS 111 data
Description: The 111 data from NECS RAIDR. This database has a restricted access and is only available to specific individuals.
Data_Sharing: Users should follow the confidentiality guidance published by the ONS, NHS disclosure control procedure and the HES protocol.
Data_Source: North of England Commissioning Support Unit (NECS), sourced from CCGs.

Name: Improving access to psychological therapies (IAPT) data
Description: The (adult) improving access to psychological therapies (IAPT) data.
Data_Sharing: The following disclosure control rules must be applied:

Description: The (adult) improving access to psychological therapies (IAPT), annual refresh data.
Data_Sharing: The following disclosure control rules must be applied:

Name: Improving access to psychological therapies (IAPT) pilot data
Description: Pilot data for the impact of 'Integrated IAPT' services co-located in and integrated with physical health services, focused on people with anxiety/depression in the context of Long Term Conditions (LTCs) and/or Medically Unexplained Symptoms (MUS).

Name: Improving access to psychological therapies (IAPT) prepublication data
Description: The prepublication version of the (adult) improving access to psychological therapies (IAPT) data. This database is restricted access.
Data_Sharing: This data is prepublication and must not be published in anyway without explicit permission from NHS Digital.

Name: Mental health data
Description: The mental health data. This includes several datasets, including the Mental Health Services Data Set (MHSDS), Mental Health Learning Disabilities Data set (MHLDDS) and Mental Health Minimum Data Set (MHMDS).
Data_Sharing: The following disclosure control rules must be applied:

Name: Mental health prepublication data
Description: The prepublication version of the mental health data. This database is restricted access.
Data_Sharing: This data is prepublication and must not be published in anyway without explicit permission from NHS Digital.

Name: Aggregate data, and standard extracts from the system
Description: An aggregated copy of the SUS+ data. This database is also used to create and store various extracts from the NCDR.
Data_Sharing: Users should follow the confidentiality guidance published by the ONS, NHS disclosure control procedure and the HES protocol.
Data_Source: Derived by NHS England, from NHS Digital data.

Name: Admitted patient care, accident & emergency and outpatient data

Data_Sharing: Users should follow the confidentiality guidance published by the ONS, NHS disclosure control procedure and the HES protocol.

Description: A number of reference tables and views that can be used independently or in conjunction with tables in other databases to provide descriptions and aggregations.
